{
  "id": "019d3411-42b0-77f0-b360-4d068ab2ea64",
  "content": "# Phase 4 Eval Framework -- Design Decisions (2026-03-28)\n\n## What: Python eval framework for A/B benchmarking retrieval configurations via hot-swap.\n\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. Python eval scripts (eval.py, compare.py) rather than Rust -- eval is tooling not product, faster iteration.\n2. Known-answer queries with source file substring matching, not UUID matching (robust across re-ingestion).\n3. Hot-swap via MCP `_meta.confirmed` for identical server conditions across A/B runs (same HNSW + tantivy index).\n4. Separate orchestrator (run-benchmark.sh) from eval (eval.py) for reusability.\n5. 15 queries across 5 categories (architecture, feature, config, api, performance), 3 per category.\n\n## Ship Gates:\n- Source Recall@5 > 50% (baseline: 37.5%)\n- MRR > 0.60 (baseline: 0.544)\n- No category regression\n- p95 latency < 20ms",
  "source_version": "mcp",
